Ok... The caption to your first clip is TOTALLY wrong. First off it's a 
Bell 407. Secondly, what do you mean "hanging around?" It's a taxiway...

cross the grass, but that makes us unpredictable and kicks up dust and 
debris that easily finds it's way into engines. Generally we only step off 
the runway over the grass if there is a fixed wing coming in behind us in 
the pattern, but generally we hover taxi. And If you actually knew about 
this video you'd know that there is no tower at that field, the Cessna, 
because of it's high wing did not see the 407, and the 407 was looking into 
the sun and as a result did not see the Cessna. Ultimately both pilots are 
at fault, the Cessna for taxiing too fast/"blind" and the 407 for taxiing 
too fast and not clearing the taxi-way before stepping off. That's why we 
have radios... To communicate... which clearly neither of them did.﻿
